% VisTools.% Version 1.7        4 Mar 2001% Handy utility functions for doing some basic tasks.% Mostly written by Lawrence K. Cormack, some functions written% by Scott B. Stevenson and added against his violent objections%% One D function generators.%	dog			- Difference of gaussians.%	gaussian	- Gaussian function.%	gab			- 1D gabor function.%	simpstim	- simple pulse function%	TimpResp	- biphasic temporal impulse response function%% Two D function generators.%	buff2arr	- 1D buffer to array conversion.%	ggaus		- 2D guassian distribution.%	ddog		- 2D difference of gaussians (eq. area)%	ggab		- 2D gabor function.%	spike		- amp. proportional to 1/distance from origin%	cone		- amp. proportional to distance from edge%% Array manipulation.%	roll		- Rolls (scrolls) rows down or up.%	turn		- Turns (pans) columns left or right.%	shift		- scrolls and pans in one call (sbs)%	autoturn	- successively offsets rows of an array%	trim		- Trims the array on all sides%	triml, %	trimr,%	trimt,%	trimb		-Trims l,r,t,or b of array by specified amount%% Image display and gamma correction%	showim		- displays an image somewhat sensibly%	graylut		- makes a gray ramp lut of specified length%	gammainv	- makes a gamma-corrected ramp LUT%	gammamap	- gamma corrects an existing LUT%	lintest		- quick verification of LUT linearity%	sky			- blue to white colormap%	splitCMap	- red-to-green map with break at the data's zero%% Image related.%	one2ff		- norms [-1 1] data to uint8 data in range [0 255].%	bumpup		- bumps [-1 1] data up to [0 1].%	coswin		- make a circular window with cosine taper%	cosbar		- elongated window with cosine cross-section%	filtnoise	- return noise filtered with a provided kernel%	oneoverf	- returns 1/f^p noise%	halfwave	- half-wave recitfies %	invert		- reverses the contrast about the dc level%	subpix		- subpixel image shift via interpolation%% Analysis%	normalize	- Normalizes elements (default range = [0-1]).%	killdc		- subtracts the average value%	filtresp	- computes static response of linear spatial filter%	ssum		- Shorthand for sum(sum())%	mmax 		- returns max of an array, i.e. max(max())%	mmin		- guess%	aave		- guess again%	geoean		- computes the geometric mean%	linefit		- Fits a straight line to x,y data (SBSteveson code?)%	ttest		- does a t-test on an Nx2 data matrix%	isodd		- tests for odd%	iseven		- tests for even%% Conversion%	d2r			- converts degrees to radians%	r2d			- converts radians to degrees%	pix2deg		- pixels to degrees%	deg2pix		- degrees to pixels%	sig2bw		- gaussian space constant to octave bandwidth%	bw2sig		- bandwidth (octaves) to gaussian space constant%	disp2blur	- retinal disparity (arcmin) to defocus (diopters)%% Miscellanious graphix%	addErrBars	- add error bars to plots and bar charts%	cls			- clears all windows created by SCREEN()	%	unitcirc	- returns n points around the unit circle%	cutlines	- removes nappy gridlines from volumetric slice plots%	xscale		- rescales x-axis of plots%	yscale		- ditto for y-axis%